<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="816" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="58.[789,1382,2479,2906]" lastBlockId="58.[176,1382,2913,3458]" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[791,1049,2601,2630]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="816" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eisentrauti">Hypsugo eisentrauti</taxonomicName>
appears to be sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[791,955,2636,2669]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="816" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassulus">H. crassulus</taxonomicName>
bellieri, with the two together sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1859" box="[933,1244,2676,2709]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nycticeinops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="816" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schlieffenii">Nycticeinops schlieffenii</taxonomicName>
, so they may be better transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hill &amp; Harrison" authorityYear="1987" box="[1218,1375,2715,2748]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nycticeinops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="816" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nycticeinops</taxonomicName>
, this generic change is not followed here, as a broad study including more species of 
<taxonomicName box="[830,942,2833,2866]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="816" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
and related genera is needed. In any case, the specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[178,359,2913,2946]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="816" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eisentrauti">H. eisentrauti</taxonomicName>
that were used in genetic studies are from 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1160,2913,2946]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
, and may actually represent H. c. bellieri instead. Several specimens attributed to this species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[234,328,2996,3025]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Congo</collectingCountry>
Basin (
<collectingCountry box="[439,591,2996,3025]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[667,786,2996,3025]" name="Rwanda" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
), East Africa (
<collectingCountry box="[988,1104,2996,3025]" name="Somalia" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1122,1235,2996,3025]" name="Uganda" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry name="Kenya" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Kenya</collectingCountry>
), and further into West Africa (
<collectingCountry box="[674,779,3031,3064]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[857,1017,3031,3064]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
) need their true identity checked; some of the specimens from the 
<collectingCountry box="[794,888,3070,3103]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Congo</collectingCountry>
Basin and 
<collectingCountry box="[1054,1167,3070,3103]" name="Somalia" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Somalia</collectingCountry>
may represent undescribed species, as they do not match the holotype of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[1018,1196,3110,3143]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="816" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eisentrauti">H. eisentrauti</taxonomicName>
. For the present, this species is considered to be restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[871,1023,3149,3182]" name="Cameroon" pageId="58" pageNumber="816">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, pending further studies. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
